[src:heat-transfer-physics/heat-equation] A fundamental solution of the heat equation is a solution that corresponds to the initial condition of an initial point source of heat at a known position.
[src:heat-transfer-physics/heat-equation] These can be used to find a general solution of the heat equation over certain domains (see, for instance, Evans 2010).
